---
---

<section class="manifesto" id="manifesto" tabindex="-1">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="display statement reveal">
      Set, setting, and&nbsp;schema<span class="dot">.</span>
    </h2>

    <div class="duo">
      <div class="body reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.1s">
        <p>
          Most software shops won’t touch this industry because the
          compliance surface scares them off, and the ones that will tend
          not to understand it. They’ll ship you a beautiful booking flow
          that violates your own protocol in three places. An AI will ship
          it even faster and understand even less.
        </p>
        <p>
          This takes years on both sides, in the engineering and in the
          field, and you shouldn’t have to translate your work for the
          people building its infrastructure. The stakes are different here
          too. A leaked customer list means a bad week for a SaaS company,
          but for a clinic or a retreat it means people’s medical and legal
          exposure. That’s why privacy gets designed in at the first schema.
        </p>
      </div>

      <figure class="diagram reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.15s">
        <svg
          viewBox="30 -34 640 254"
          role="img"
          aria-label="The skeletal structure of psilocybin, annotated with code-review comments: the phosphate group is marked 'removed at runtime', the indole core 'base class shared with serotonin', and the dimethyl side chain 'the business logic'"
        >
          <g class="stroke">
            <!-- indole: benzene ring -->
            <path d="M60 92 L100 69 L140 92 L140 138 L100 161 L60 138 Z" />
            <!-- aromatic inner bonds -->
            <path d="M104 78 L133 95" />
            <path d="M133 135 L104 152" />
            <path d="M67 132 L67 98" />
            <!-- fused pyrrole -->
            <path d="M140 92 L183 79 L210 115 L183 151 L140 138" />
            <!-- C2=C3 double bond -->
            <path d="M186 88 L206 114" />
            <!-- side chain: C3 → CH2 → CH2 → N -->
            <path d="M183 79 L212 52 L246 66 L272 46" />
            <!-- N-methyls -->
            <path d="M287 40 L316 50" />
            <path d="M282 32 L288 12" />
            <!-- 4-phosphoryloxy bond -->
            <path d="M100 69 L100 44" />
          </g>
          <g class="label">
            <text x="183" y="168">NH</text>
            <text x="279" y="47">N</text>
            <text x="100" y="34">OPO₃H₂</text>
          </g>

          <!-- code-review annotations -->
          <g class="leader">
            <path d="M132 24 L182 -10" />
            <path d="M322 51 L368 68" />
            <path d="M212 128 L368 150" />
          </g>
          <g class="comment">
            <text x="188" y="-6">// removed at runtime</text>
            <text x="374" y="72">// the business logic</text>
            <text x="374" y="154">// base class shared with serotonin</text>
          </g>
        </svg>
        <figcaption class="mono">fig. 01 — psilocybin, annotated like a code review</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .manifesto {
    /* the one violet room in the green house — the altered-state argument
       gets the altered surface; same luminance band as --void-deep */
    background: oklch(0.235 0.075 300);
    padding-block: var(--space-section);
  }

  /* scroll target only — the ring belongs on controls, not sections */
  .manifesto:focus-visible { outline: none; }

  .statement {
    font-size: var(--text-h2);
    max-width: 16ch;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .dot { color: var(--acid); }

  .duo {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: clamp(3rem, 7vh, 4.5rem);
    margin-block-start: clamp(3rem, 7vh, 5rem);
    align-items: center;
  }

  @media (min-width: 60rem) {
    .duo {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.05fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
      column-gap: clamp(3rem, 6vw, 6rem);
    }
    /* diagram left, argument right — no orphaned corners */
    .diagram { order: -1; }
  }

  .body { max-width: 34em; }
  .body p { margin: 0; }
  .body p + p { margin-block-start: 1.2em; }

  .diagram {
    margin: 0;
  }

  .diagram svg {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 36rem;
    height: auto;
  }

  .stroke path {
    fill: none;
    stroke: var(--ink);
    stroke-width: 1.5;
    stroke-linecap: round;
    stroke-linejoin: round;
  }

  .label text {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    fill: var(--ink);
    text-anchor: middle;
  }

  .leader path {
    fill: none;
    stroke: var(--ink-faint);
    stroke-width: 1;
    stroke-dasharray: 1 5;
    stroke-linecap: round;
  }

  .comment text {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12.5px;
    fill: var(--acid);
  }

  figcaption {
    margin-block-start: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--ink-dim);
  }
</style>
